00:00:14.260 --> 00:00:16.280
So, for example the equation

00:00:16.280 --> 00:00:19.704
y is equal to two x minus three,

00:00:19.704 --> 00:00:22.607
this is a linear equation.

00:00:22.607 --> 00:00:25.439
Now why do we call it a linear equation?

00:00:25.439 --> 00:00:27.850
Well if you were to take
the set of all of the

00:00:27.850 --> 00:00:30.903
xy pairs that satisfy this equation

00:00:30.903 --> 00:00:33.387
and if you were to graph
them on the coordinate plane,

00:00:33.387 --> 00:00:35.709
you would actually get a line.

00:00:35.709 --> 00:00:37.764
That's why it's called a linear equation.

00:00:37.764 --> 00:00:39.946
And let's actually feel
good about that statement.

00:00:39.946 --> 00:00:43.589
Let's see, let's plot some of the xy pairs

00:00:43.589 --> 00:00:46.283
