00:00:50.436 --> 00:00:53.617
make it easy to calculate
the corresponding y values.

00:00:53.617 --> 00:00:55.672
So, if x is equal to zero

00:00:55.672 --> 00:00:58.771
y is gonna be two times zero minus three

00:00:58.771 --> 00:01:00.652
which is negative three.

00:01:00.652 --> 00:01:03.090
And on our coordinate plane here that's--

00:01:03.090 --> 00:01:04.773
we're gonna move zero in the x direction,

00:01:04.773 --> 00:01:06.154
zero in the horizontal direction

00:01:06.154 --> 00:01:08.168
and we're gonna go down three
in the vertical direction,

00:01:08.168 --> 00:01:09.178
in the y direction.

00:01:09.178 --> 00:01:11.406
So, that's that point there.

00:01:11.406 --> 00:01:14.611
If x is equal to one, what is y equal to?

00:01:14.611 --> 00:01:19.611
Well two times one is two,
minus three is negative one.

00:01:19.707 --> 00:01:22.110
So we move positive one in the x direction

00:01:22.110 --> 00:01:25.790
and negative one, or down
one, in the y direction.

00:01:25.790 --> 00:01:29.772
Now let's see, if x is
equal to two what is y?

00:01:29.772 --> 00:01:33.231
Two times two is four, minus three is one.

00:01:33.231 --> 00:01:37.654
