and non-linear equations,

00:07:03.057 --> 00:07:04.933
let's see if we can come
up with a definition for

00:07:04.933 --> 00:07:05.757
linear equations.

00:07:05.757 --> 00:07:07.649
One way to think about is it's an equation

00:07:07.649 --> 00:07:09.751
that if you were to graph
all of the x and y pairs that

00:07:09.751 --> 00:07:11.028
satisfy this equation,

00:07:11.028 --> 00:07:12.316
you'll get a line.

00:07:12.316 --> 00:07:13.415
And that's actually
literally where the word

00:07:13.415 --> 00:07:15.191
linear equation comes from.

00:07:15.191 --> 00:07:16.805
But another way to think about it is

00:07:16.805 --> 00:07:18.407
it's going to be an equation where

00:07:18.407 --> 00:07:21.146
every term is either
going to be a constant,

00:07:21.146 --> 00:07:23.054
so for example, twelve is a constant.

00:07:23.054 --> 00:07:24.967
It's not going to change
based on the value of

00:07:24.967 --> 00:07:27.232
some variable, twelve is twelve.

00:07:27.232 --> 00:07:29.495
Or negative three is negative three.

00:07:29.495 --> 00:07:31.550
So every term is either
going to be a constant

00:07:31.550 --> 00:07:35.416
or it's going to be a
constant times a variable

00:07:35.416 --> 00:07:37.111
raised to the first power.

00:07:37.111 --> 00:07:40.710
So this is the constant two
times x to the first power.

00:07:40.710 --> 00:07:43.670
This is the variable y
raised to the first power.

00:07:43.670 --> 00:07:46.131
You could say that bceause
this is just one y.

00:07:46.131 --> 00:07:48.476
We're not dividing by x or y,

00:07:48.476 --> 00:07:49.950
we're not multiplying,

00:07:49.950 --> 00:07:52.853
we don't have a term that
has x to the second power,

00:07:52.853 --> 00:07:55.374
or x to the third power,
or y to the fifth power.

00:07:55.374 --> 00:07:57.568
We just have y to the first power,

00:07:57.568 --> 00:07:58.671
we have x to the first power.

00:07:58.671 --> 00:08:00.579
We're not multiplying x and y together

00:08:00.579 --> 00:08:02.227
like we did over here.

00:08:02.227 --> 00:08:03.226
So if every--

00:08:03.226 --> 00:08:05.164
if every term in your equation,

00:08:05.164 --> 00:08:06.363
on either side of the equation,

00:08:06.363 --> 00:08:10.566
is either a constant or its
just some number times x,

00:08:10.566 --> 00:08:13.406
just x to the first power
or some number times y,

00:08:13.406 --> 00:08:15.554
and you're not multiplying
your x's and y's together

00:08:15.554 --> 00:08:18.903
you are dealing with a linear equation.

